window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Everything canâ€™t be about school....</b></p> <p>The third-year students are about to take on those who know them best.</p> <p>Each other.</p> <p>Using a variation of the classic game of Capture the Flag, Kaiden and his friends must join teams and battle each other.</p> <p>It is time for Kaiden to learn what it means to lead.</p> <p>Then, when they are out on the town, an opportunity is handed to the students on a silver platter.</p> <p>Kaiden has a job offer to help protect a business in San Diego, but he needs more members. Will the students join him?</p> <p>If they do join him, will they survive? Few of the other students have taken on outside jobs like Kaiden has.</p> <p>Further, will the teachers find out about it?</p> <p>You don't become the best of the best by staying alive. In the Animus, you are closer to perfection with each death you suffer.</p> <p>Kaiden Jericho would rather skip the death part, thank you very much.</p> <p><i>Includes special note from co-author Michael Anderle.</i></p>"; 
